Gol Reduced to ‘Neutral’ From ‘Buy’ at BofA on Lower Guidance

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-07-29T12:56:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/gol-reduced-to-neutral-from-buy-at-bofa-on-lower-guidance.html
Gol Linhas Aereas Inteligentes SA
was cut to “neutral” from “buy” at Bank of America Corp.
after the Brazilian airline reduced some of its 2011 forecasts.  Bank of America lowered its earnings-per-share estimate for
Gol this year to 46 cents from 81 cents, analysts Sara Delfim
and Roberto Otero wrote in a note to clients.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in  Sao Paulo  at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos in New York at 
 papadopoulous@bloomberg.net  